+From fe80096f01779906bb0f549acd412d3a70ce2237 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
+From: Juniper Bevensee <juniperbevensee@users.noreply.github.com>
+Date: Fri, 22 May 2026 11:04:56 +1200
+Subject: [PATCH 1/3] feat: add context_id memory scoping for
+ per-channel/tenant isolation
+
+Adds an opaque context_id parameter to MemoryStore that routes memory
+writes to per-context subdirectories (memories/contexts/{context_id}/).
+Reads merge global + context-scoped entries. Backwards-compatible:
+context_id=None preserves existing single-tenant behavior exactly.
+
+Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
